# Truth Tables for Arguments: Exercises

:::auto-tally
:::

# Fix the Errors

```{.TruthTable .Validity options="nocounterexample turnstilemark" points=10}
E8.1 P, Q :|-: R
|    T  T  T   T
|    T  T  T   F
|    T  F  F   T
|    T  F  F   F
|    F  T  F   T
|    F  T  F   F
|    F  F  F   T
|    F  F  F   F
E8.2 P, Q :|-: P
|    T  T  T   T
|    T  F  F   T
|    F  T  T   F
|    F  F  F   F
E8.3 P->Q, Q :|-: P
|    TT T  T  T   T
|    TF F  F  F   T
|    FT T  T  T   F
|    FT F  F  F   F
E8.4 P\/Q, Q :|-: ~P
|    TF T  T  T   FT
|    TT F  F  T   FT
|    FT T  T  T   TF
|    FF F  F  T   TF
E8.5 ~(P/\Q) :|-: ~(P<->Q)
|    F T TT   F   F T T T
|    T T FF   T   T T F F
|    T F FT   T   T F F T
|    T F FF   T   F F T F
```

# Equivalence and Consistency

```{.TruthTable .Simple options="nocounterexample" points=10}
E8.6 ~P->~Q, Q->P
```
```{.QualitativeProblem .MultipleSelection points=10}
E8.7 These two sentences are:
| *truth-functionally equivalent
| not truth-functionally equivalent
| *truth-functionally consistent
| truth-functionally inconsistent
```

```{.TruthTable .Simple options="nocounterexample" points=10}
E8.8 ~P->~Q, P->Q
```
```{.QualitativeProblem .MultipleSelection points=10}
E8.9 These two sentences are:
| truth-functionally equivalent
| *not truth-functionally equivalent
| *truth-functionally consistent
| truth-functionally inconsistent
```

```{.TruthTable .Simple options="nocounterexample" points=10}
E8.10 ~(P/\Q), ~P/\~Q
```
```{.QualitativeProblem .MultipleSelection points=10}
E8.11 These two sentences are:
| truth-functionally equivalent
| *not truth-functionally equivalent
| *truth-functionally consistent
| truth-functionally inconsistent
```

```{.TruthTable .Simple options="nocounterexample" points=10}
E8.12 P<->Q, P/\~Q
```
```{.QualitativeProblem .MultipleSelection points=10}
E8.13 These two sentences are:
| truth-functionally equivalent
| *not truth-functionally equivalent
| truth-functionally consistent
| *truth-functionally inconsistent
```

```{.TruthTable .Simple options="nocounterexample" points=10}
